# Dual Licensing Model

## 1. Commercial License (Enterprise License)

**License Fee:** $500 per instance per year

This license grants organizations, enterprises, and corporations the right to use, modify, and integrate Smart Scheduler into their commercial products and services.

**Permitted Uses:**
- Use in commercial products and services
- Modification of the source code
- Integration with other commercial systems
- Internal and external deployment
- Support and maintenance rights

**Restrictions:**
- Source code must not be disclosed or distributed
- Derivative works are owned by the licensee
- No redistribution of the software without permission

**Payment Terms:**
- Annual payment of $500 per instance
- License is non-exclusive
- License can be renewed annually

For commercial licensing inquiries, please contact the project maintainer.

## 2. Research License (Free for Non-Commercial Research)

**License Fee:** Free

This license grants educational institutions, research organizations, and individual researchers the right to use Smart Scheduler for non-commercial research, educational, and academic purposes.

**Permitted Uses:**
- Use in academic research
- Educational purposes in universities and schools
- Peer-reviewed publication of research results
- Modification for research purposes
- Non-commercial deployment
- Internal institutional use

**Restrictions:**
- Cannot be used for commercial purposes or services
- Cannot be integrated into commercial products
- Source code modifications must be clearly documented
- Research results must acknowledge this project

**Conditions:**
- Academic or research affiliation verification may be required
- Attribution and proper citation required in all publications
- Any modifications must be made available to the original project (optional but encouraged)

## 3. General Terms

**Disclaimer:**
THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NONINFRINGEMENT.

**Governing Law:**
This license is governed by applicable laws in the jurisdiction where the project maintainer resides.

**Termination:**
Licenses may be terminated if the licensee violates the terms of the agreement.

**Determining Use Type:**
- **Commercial Use:** Any use that generates revenue or is part of a for-profit operation
- **Research Use:** Use for academic study, scientific investigation, or educational purposes by accredited institutions or researchers

For questions about which license applies to your use case, please contact the project maintainer.
